race.comment: ZEALOUSLY (5) just under six-weeks between runs for this after being nailed late when third in the G2 Caulfield Sprint on October 18. Will race handy and prove hard to hold out. FLYING FOR FUN (8) underrated mare who drops massively in grade after battling in the heavy going when seventh over 1200m in the G1 Champions Sprint at Flemington. Will relish the fast tempo and can finish over the top of these. FRONT PAGE (1) returns from a let-up, second-up. Anchored with the 60kg when a gallant sixth in the Kosciuszko over 1200m at Randwick. Stable rider hops on and sure to be thereabouts. A LITTLE DEEP (2) talented mare resuming. Undefeated in four first up starts and saves her best for this trip. Proven at Group level and the two trials had merit. Gets every chance from the draw. OUROBOROS (11) improving sprinter who comes down from Queensland. Kept up to the mark with a trial win over 1000m at Doomben. Sits on the limit and not to be underestimated.
